    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The 3-midline-ports technique is a safety approach and associates lower postoperative pain,
      when compared with the standard &quot;French&quot; technique.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The patients will be randomized into 2 groups: those patients undergoing laparoscopic
      cholecystectomy following the &quot;French&quot; technique (Group 1) and those ones undergoing the
      3-midline-ports approach (Group 2).
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
